## Description

A random variable X is normally distributed with mean \mew and variance \sigma if it has the probability density function of X as:




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
1 + 1
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
[1] 2
```
:::
:::
